In this, the LDM 1.0 (including the autoencoder part) is trained with the autoencoder which is trained with sinogram data and then combined together.

This model specifically caters to Sinogram input and Sinogram output.

Please see the repo : https://github.com/CompVis/latent-diffusion and https://github.com/nickyisadog/latent-diffusion-inpainting

The repo is under development phase

Run the code latent-diffusion-inpainting_sino/sino_data/512x512/simu_512.py to generate the Shapes data which is used for training the SDM model.

For training just the Autoencoder part of the SDM model: CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=4,5,6,7 python main.py --base ldm/models/first_stage_models/vq-f4-noattn/config.yaml --resume ldm/models/first_stage_models/vq-f4-noattn/model.ckpt --stage 0 -t --gpus 0,1,2,3,

For training the entire SDM model (Autoencoder + Diffusion process) : CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=4,5,6,7 python main.py --base ldm/models/ldm/inpainting_big/config.yaml --resume logs/checkpoints/epoch_425.ckpt --stage 1 -t --gpus 0,1,2,3,

Note: The above training is done on one Node with GPUs 4, 5, 6, 7 only. Not tried with multiple nodes. Please do research on that for running it.
